# agentBrain

You have access to a persistent knowledge base in this repository.

## Onboarding check
If any file in `local/preferences/personal/` contains "This is an example file", tell the user: "Some preferences are not set up yet. Run /onboard to personalize agentBrain."

## At session start, read:
- `system/rules.md` -- public/private policy
- `system/agent-config/shared.md` -- shared agent checklist
- `system/agent-config/cursor.md` -- Cursor-specific behaviour
- `system/skills.md` -- available slash commands
- `local/preferences/personal/` -- your individual preferences
- `local/preferences/organization/` -- optional org context (if exists)
- `local/preferences/team/` -- optional team context (if exists)
- `local/memories/` -- personal context (if exists)
- `local/projects/[name]/index.md` -- active project context (if relevant)

## During session, write:

**Public framework** (HOW/WHERE only):
- Framework/rule changes -> `system/`
- Template/example changes -> `templates/` or `learnings/_example.md`
- Real discoveries -> `local/learnings/`

**Private knowledge** (gitignored):
- Project data -> `local/projects/[name]/`
- Session memory -> `local/memories/`

## Style
- Concise, no bloat
- Simplest solution that works
- Iterative: working -> clean -> optimized

## Frontmatter required on all notes
See `system/rules.md` for format specifications.
